title: Act2_EveIntro_P2N1
---
/// no repeat
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Oh good, you’re awake!
Eve: Ah! Sorry, I didn’t mean to scare you.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]It's really repeating...[/i]
Cyrus: [i]If I want to stop the Assimilation, I need to know more about this world.[/i]
===


title: Act2_SecretPoliceIntro_P2N3
---
/// no repeat
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: You actually did it. Are you a Hunter?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I’d like to be.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Hmm...we could make a pretty good team~

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: At protecting the town or collecting the bounties?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Why not both? Let’s get you suited up.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: That way looks dangerous, let’s try another path.

<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
: [i]Some time later...[/i]
Transition (TODO)

<<set_portrait YarnManager Tobias>>
???: Is that you, Eve?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Hey! Didn’t expect to run into you two.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
???: Who’s this?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Cyrus, a soon-to-be Hunter.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
???: Ah, I can tell you all you need to know. You happen to be in the presence of a master.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Tobias>>
Tobias: I’m Tobias, you can ignore Saul.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: He’s just jealous.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Tobias>>
Tobias: Better head back, Eve. You know what your father would say about being out here.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: Not like the city is much safer, probably festering with False Humans.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Tobias>>
Tobias: What's paranoia good for? All it’s done is drive everyone crazy accusing each other.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: It’s not paranoia, my neighbor’s definitely been acting strange.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: What’s a False Human?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Oh, uh, Cyrus is new here.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: They’re the most dangerous kind of memory monster, they look and act just like us. Just one of them can wipe out a whole fleet of Hunters.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Tobias>>
Tobias: That’s why we’re paid to take care of the little guys, so The Ministry of Prismatic Security can focus on tracking down the False Humans.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: Supposedly. I wish they’d hurry up and do their job before the Assimilation ends us all.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]If I find the False Human, could I stop the Assimilation?[/i]
Cyrus: How do I contact Prismatic Security?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Tobias>>
Tobias: [i]“And a new dawn rises”.[/i] Use that code if you ever run into something bigger than you can handle.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: Alright, let’s get moving. We’ve got a hunt to finish.
===


title: Act2_ShopBanter_P2N5
---

<<set_portrait YarnManager Shopkeeper>>
Shopkeeper: Eve? Where have you been?!

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Had a run-in with some monsters, but we handled it. (Banter continues)

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]The fates here were quite helpful. I should take a look.[/i]


<<set_portrait YarnManager Shopkeeper>>
Shopkeeper: You ought to take a look at my wares then. Don’t want you getting killed either.
Shopkeeper: Here, I’ve got all the Fates a Hunter could ask for.

<<open_shop YarnManager>>
<<wait_for_shop_close YarnManager>>
<<jump Act2_ShopBanter_N5>>
===

