title: Act2_ShopBanter_Family
---
    <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
    Cyrus: Your dad seems... nice.

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
    Eve: He likes to act tough, but he’s really just terrified.

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
    Cyrus: He mentioned you had a sister?

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
    Eve: ...
    Eve: Ava.
    Eve: She’s not here anymore.

    -> Inquire further
        <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
        Cyrus: Oh. Is she...

        <<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
        Eve: We snuck out to the outskirts together, but we were too young to know what we were getting into.
        Eve: When the monsters came, I just ran.

        <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
        Cyrus: Oh...I’m sorry.
        <<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
        Eve: Yeah, I am too.
        <<jump Act2_ShopBanter_End>>
    -> Change the topic
        <<jump Act2_ShopBanter_End>>
===


title: Act2_ShopBanter_Dispatcher
---
    <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
    Cyrus: You have experience with this?
    <<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
    Eve: Scared I’m gonna get you killed?
    Eve: This is my first time, but I’ve helped Hunters before, patching gear, pointing them to jobs, you name it.
    <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
    Cyrus: Why’d you decide to be a dispatcher now?

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
    Eve: I’ve always wanted to do more to help around here, and you looked like you were going to get yourself killed without someone watching your back.
    <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
    Cyrus: Won’t argue with that.

<<jump Act2_ShopBanter_End>>
===


title: Act2_ShopBanter_Prism
---
    <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
    Cyrus: Is it always this tense around here?

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
    Eve: Lately? Yeah. Memory monsters keep spawning faster than we can kill them. And like Tobias said, a lot of people don’t trust each other anymore.

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
    Cyrus: You think he’s right, that it’s all just paranoia?

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
    Eve: ...I think the one thing this city needs right now is a united front.

<<jump Act2_ShopBanter_End>>
===


title: Act2_ShopBanter_Eve
---
    <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
    Cyrus: So, uh, you do anything besides work?

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
    Eve: Dad thinks it’s silly, but I like to make things out of the scraps laying around the shop.

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
    Cyrus: You mean the sculptures? You made these?

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
    Eve: They’re a work in progress. I like to find a purpose for misfit things, rather than just throw them out.
    Eve: What do you do?

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
    Cyrus: ...
    Cyrus: Good question.

    <<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
    Eve: Huh? It’s not like you were just born today.

<<jump Act2_ShopBanter_End>>
===


title: Act2_ShopBanter_End
---
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
: [i]ding[/i]
Eve: That was fast, your first mission’s already here.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Deeper in the outskirts?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Good guess. Let’s head out.
===


title: Act2_PoliceContact_PreCombat_P2N6
---
/// no repeat
<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: Cyrus! Didn’t expect to see you so soon! Looks like every Hunter is getting sent out here.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Why would we all be dispatched so far away at the same time? 

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: It was a government commission, mayor’s orders. Must be serious.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]Seems like my suspicions were true.[/i]
===


title: Act2_PoliceContact_PostCombat_P2N6
---
/// no repeat
<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Eve?
Cyrus: [i]Connection cut off again... maybe Prismatic Security can help.[/i]
Cyrus: Hello?

???: The moon falls.

Cyrus: And a new dawn rises.

???: What are you calling to report?

Cyrus: The mayor is a False Human.

???: ...
???: And what makes you so sure of this?

Cyrus: He just dispatched all the Hunters deep into the outskirts, the city’s been left undefended for something terrible.

???: We don’t waste our time on every far-flung theory.

Cyrus: Look, I know it sounds crazy, but if I’m wrong, you lose an hour. If I’m right, you lose a city.

???: ...

: [i]signal cut[/i] 

Cyrus: [i]How am I supposed to warn people about something that hasn’t happened yet?[/i]
===


